Dynamic solution using [Element#className][1], [String#replace][2].

Idea is to get the element, get the full className and dynamically increment the number by replacing it with the next number (using modulo to make sure it doesn&#39;t go over the max number of backgrounds available).

The `Math.max` is after the increment gets to `5` to ensure that we don&#39;t start with `0`.

&lt;!-- begin snippet: js hide: false console: true babel: false --&gt;

&lt;!-- language: lang-js --&gt;

    const limit = 5;
    $(&#39;.arrow-next&#39;).click(function() {
      const ele = $(&quot;.background&quot;).get(0);

      ele.className = ele
        .className
        .replace(
          /background-([0-9])/g, 
          (_, p1) =&gt; &#39;background-&#39; + Math.max((Number(p1) + 1) % limit, 1)
        );
    });

